        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:28PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Timpas, or 13 miles west of La Junta, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Junta, Rocky Ford, Swink, and Timpas.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
